59    /**
60    * Implementations of AbstractCommandLineRunner translate flags into Java
61    * API calls on the Compiler. AbstractCompiler contains common flags and logic
62    * to make that happen.
63    *
64    * This class may be extended and used to create other Java classes
65    * that behave the same as running the Compiler from the command line. Example:
66    *
67    * <pre>
68    * class MyCommandLineRunner extends
69    * AbstractCommandLineRunner<MyCompiler, MyOptions> {
70    * MyCommandLineRunner(String[] args) {
71    * super(args);
72    * }
73    *
74    * &#064;Override
75    * protected MyOptions createOptions() {
76    * MyOptions options = new MyOptions();
77    * CompilerFlagTranslator.setOptionsFromFlags(options);
78    * addMyCrazyCompilerPassThatOutputsAnExtraFile(options);
79    * return options;
80    * }
81    *
82    * &#064;Override
83    * protected MyCompiler createCompiler() {
84    * return new MyCompiler();
85    * }
86    *
87    * public static void main(String[] args) {
88    * (new MyCommandLineRunner(args)).run();
89    * }
90    * }
91    * </pre>
92    *
93    * @author bolinfest@google.com (Michael Bolin)
94    */
 
59.6% Uncovered Elements: 346 (857) Complexity: 215 Complexity Density: 0.41
